Sentencas: This study explored CO as a primary fuel in anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) of both tubular and planar geometries.
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Tubular single cells with active areas of 24 cm(2) generated power up to 16W. Open circuit voltages for various CO/CO2 mixture compositions agreed well with the expected values.
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In flowing dry CO, power densities up to 0.67 W cm(-2) were achieved at 1 A cm(-2) and 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This performance compared well with 0.74 W cm(-2) measured for pure H-2 in the same cell and under the same operating conditions.
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Performance stability of tubular cells was investigated by long-term testing in flowing CO during which no carbon deposition was observed.
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: At a constant current of 9.96 A (or, 0.414 A cm(-2)) power output remained unchanged over 375 h of continuous operation at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In addition, a 50-cell planar SOFC stack was operated at 800 degrees C on 95% CO (balance CO2), which generated 1176W of total power at a power density of 224 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that CO is a viable primary fuel for SOFCs.
Titulo: Carbon monoxide-fueled solid oxide fuel cell
